  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A burst of cold energy emanates from you in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [[/r 3d8]] cold damage and is hindered by ice formations for 1 minute, or until it or another creature within reach of it uses an action to break away the ice. A creature hindered by ice has its speed reduced to 0. On a successful save, a creature takes half as much damage and isn't hindered by ice.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p>The cold freezes nonmagical liquids in the area that are not being worn or carried.</p></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner\"><strong>At Higher Levels</strong>. </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, increase the cold damage by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 2nd.</p></div></div>",
